In our case, the map is `torusEmb : Diag Spec(𝕜) (GrothendieckAddGroup M) → Diag Spec(𝕜) M`. We need to show that the image of this map is dense in `Diag Spec(𝕜) M`.

The image of the torus under the embedding should be the entire space `Diag Spec(𝕜) M`. This is because the torus is the group of units of the monoid `M` (if `M` is a group), and the embedding is likely the natural one. The image should indeed be the entire space.

